Web Developer, Job #9662		KCTCS		Lexington, Kentucky Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong> </strong> </p><p><strong> </strong> </p><p><strong>Position Description</strong> </p><p>The Web Developer will develop and manage websites, databases and applications that are used to support, streamline and enhance KCTCS’s marketing and recruitment efforts. </p><p>  </p><p>KCTCS offers a competitive benefits package and an attractive work environment that supports excellence, innovation and creativity. Positions with the KCTCS System Office are term-contract positions, with the expectancy of continuance based on performance. </p><p>  </p><p><strong>Major Responsibilities/Duties</strong> </p><ul><li>Provide technical assistance on web projects including some website design. </li><li>Provide support and assist in the development of features to be used within the KCTCS Content Management System (CMS). </li><li>Manage the transfer of data into marketing databases from various sources; including integration with external sources, and auditing the results for accuracy and documenting procedures and policies. </li><li>Administer CRM, reporting, dashboards and analytics systems. Responsibilities include user management, configuration, testing and customizing features to maximize use of the marketing database(s) and work closely with IT, other departments. </li><li>Establish best practices; maintain knowledge of current developments in new technologies, trends, and emerging web standards; and to incorporate this knowledge into the department. </li><li>Provide backup emergency support for KCTCS’s CMS. </li><li>Other duties as assigned. </li></ul><p>  </p><p><strong>Minimum Requirements</strong> </p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree and three (3) years of position-related experience, or equivalent. </li></ul><p>  </p><p><strong>Preferred Competencies</strong>   </p><ul><li>Four (4) years of position-related experience; </li><li>Must have proficient computer skills and comfortable with new technology </li><li>Must have exceptional organizational skills and be detailed oriented </li></ul><p>  </p><p>  </p><p>  </p><p>KY law requires state and national pre-employment background checks as a condition of employment.<br /> </p><p>All materials must be received by close of business on 8/27/2015 </p><p>  </p><p>Applicants will be notified if selected for an interview. </p><p>Search may be extended if additional candidates are needed. </p><p>  </p><p>For questions regarding the above position, contact us by emailing <br /> Kctcs.employ.request@kctcs.edu</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>A Statewide System<br /> <br />The Kentucky Community and Technical College System (KCTCS) is the newest postsecondary education institution in the Commonwealth. KCTCS was created by the Kentucky Postsecondary Education Improvement Act of 1997 (House Bill 1). Our 16 colleges and on 68 campuses are deeply rooted in the educational history and tradition of Kentucky. July 1, 2008, marked the 10th anniversary of the unification of Kentucky’s postsecondary community colleges and technical institutions, some dating back to the early 1900’s.</p></div>